
     =========================================================
     Geant4 - an Object-Oriented Toolkit for Simulation in HEP
     =========================================================

                CMS Calorimeter benchmark History file
                --------------------------------------
This file should be used by the G4 example coordinator to briefly
summarize all major modifications introduced in the code and keep
track of all tags.

     ----------------------------------------------------------
     * Reverse chronological order (last date on top), please *

     ----------------------------------------------------------

14-Dec-2012 - A.Ribon (cmscal-V09-06-01)
---------------------
Removed LHEP physics list.

10-Dec-2012 - A.Ribon (cmscal-V09-06-00)
---------------------
Removed obsolete physics lists.

23-Nov-2012 - G.Folger (cmscal-V09-05-02)
---------------------
-  add testing for FTFP_BERT_HP
-  Increase statistic to 100 events for QGSP_BERT and FTFP_BERT

12-Oct-2012 - G.Cosmo (cmscal-V09-05-01)
---------------------
Explicit inclusion of units and constants headers.

5 Jul 2012 - Pere Mato (cmscal-V09-05-00)
---------------------
Replaced QGSP_INCL_ABLA by QGSP_INCLXX in the tests of HadCalCMS 

14 Nov 2011 - Pere Mato (cmscal-V09-04-01)
---------------------
Removed QGSP_BERT_TRV QGSP_BERT_NOLEP from the tests of HadCalCMS 

05 Oct 2011 - Andrea Dotti (cmscal-V09-04-00)
---------------------
Removed set but not used variables (GCC 4.6 warning)


24 Mar 2010 - A.Ribon (cmscal-V09-03-00)
---------------------
- Use <ctime> header (instead of <time.h>) in main().
- Added new macro files with different number of events: 100, 500, 1k
  (i.e. 1000) and 5k (i.e. 5000).

18 Mar 2010 - A.Ribon
---------------------
- Changed main for Windows compatibility: added header <time.h>, and removed
  call to G4UItcsh.
- Macro files run*.g4 run now 5 events (instead of 1).

12 Nov 2009 - A.Ribon (cmscal-V09-02-03)
---------------------
- The Physics List is still set via command line argument, e.g :
     mainHadCalo run1.g4 QGSP_BIC 
  but it uses the G4PhysListFactory, so there is no need to
  update the main program with new/obsolete Physics Lists.


19 Aug 2009 - A.Ribon (cmscal-V09-02-02)
---------------------
- The Physics List is now set via command line argument, e.g :
     mainHadCalo run1.g4 QGSP_BIC 


16 Jul 2009 - A.Ribon (cmscal-V09-02-01)
---------------------
- Added three Geant4 macro files to be used for nightly tests.


16 Jul 2009 - A.Ribon (cmscal-V09-02-00)
---------------------
- The Physics List is now set via the environmental variable
  PHYSLIST.


23 Oct 2007 - A.Ribon (cmscal-V09-00-00)
---------------------
- Created.
